trans-unit.source: Provides data for the <xref href="System.Web.Profile.ProfileModule.Personalize"></xref> event of the <xref href="System.Web.Profile.ProfileModule"></xref> class.
You can use the <xref:System.Web.Profile.ProfileEventArgs> class during the <xref:System.Web.Profile.ProfileModule.Personalize> event to specify a custom user profile.

If, when the <xref:System.Web.Profile.ProfileModule.Personalize> event completes, the <xref:System.Web.Profile.ProfileEventArgs> parameter of the <xref:System.Web.Profile.ProfileEventHandler> has its <xref:System.Web.Profile.ProfileEventArgs.Profile%2A> property set to a value that’s not `null`, then the <xref:System.Web.Profile.ProfileModule> uses the value of the <xref:System.Web.Profile.ProfileEventArgs.Profile%2A> property in the current <xref:System.Web.HttpContext>.
Creates an instance of the <xref href="System.Web.Profile.ProfileEventArgs"></xref> class.

The <xref:System.Web.Profile.ProfileEventArgs.%23ctor%2A> creates an instance of the <xref:System.Web.Profile.ProfileEventArgs> class and sets the <xref:System.Web.Profile.ProfileEventArgs.Context%2A> property to the specified <xref:System.Web.HttpContext>.
The <xref href="System.Web.HttpContext"></xref> of the current request.
Gets the <xref href="System.Web.HttpContext"></xref> for the current request.
The <xref:System.Web.Profile.ProfileEventArgs> object provides event information to the <xref:System.Web.Profile.ProfileModule.Personalize> event of the <xref:System.Web.Profile.ProfileModule> class.
The <xref:System.Web.Profile.ProfileEventArgs.Context%2A> property provides access to the <xref:System.Web.HttpContext> of the current request.
The <xref href="System.Web.HttpContext"></xref> for the current request
Gets or sets the user profile for the current request.
You can use the <xref:System.Web.Profile.ProfileEventArgs.Profile%2A> property during the <xref:System.Web.Profile.ProfileModule.Personalize> event to specify a custom user profile.

If, when the <xref:System.Web.Profile.ProfileModule.Personalize> event completes, the <xref:System.Web.Profile.ProfileEventArgs> parameter of the <xref:System.Web.Profile.ProfileEventHandler> has its <xref:System.Web.Profile.ProfileEventArgs.Profile%2A> property set to a value that’s not `null`, then the <xref:System.Web.Profile.ProfileModule> uses the value of the <xref:System.Web.Profile.ProfileEventArgs.Profile%2A> property in the current <xref:System.Web.HttpContext>.
The <xref:System.Web.Profile.ProfileModule> does not set the <xref:System.Web.Profile.ProfileEventArgs.Profile%2A> property for the <xref:System.Web.Profile.ProfileModule.Personalize> event.

The <xref:System.Web.Profile.ProfileModule> only gets the value of the <xref:System.Web.Profile.ProfileEventArgs.Profile%2A> property when the code in the <xref:System.Web.Profile.ProfileModule.Personalize> event completes.

If the <xref:System.Web.Profile.ProfileEventArgs.Profile%2A?displayProperty=fullName> property is not explicitly set by application code during the <xref:System.Web.Profile.ProfileModule.Personalize> event, the <xref:System.Web.Profile.ProfileEventArgs.Profile%2A> property value will be `null`.
The user profile to use for the current request.
